{"id": 21116, "date": "2020-09-22T05:00:00", "date_gmt": "2020-09-22T12:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=21116"}, "modified": "2020-09-19T11:36:58", "modified_gmt": "2020-09-19T18:36:58", "slug": "roll-of-the-dice-mississippi", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2020/09/22/roll-of-the-dice-mississippi/", "title": {"rendered": "Roll of the Dice: Mississippi"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Bruce adapted classic literature in song long before &#8220;<a href=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/10/17/roll-of-the-dice-the-ghost-of-tom-joad/\">The Ghost of Tom Joad.</a>&#8221;</p>\n<p>In the autumn of 1968, nineteen-year-old Bruce Springsteen put pen to paper and wrote a song called &#8220;Mississippi,&#8221; featuring two friends drifting down the great river on a raft on a beautiful, lazy summer day. One of them was named Jim, and although the narrator never identifies himself, it&#8217;s not too difficult to figure out his name, too.</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\"><em>Sailing down the Mississippi</em><br />\n<em>Chewing on a piece of hay</em><br />\n<em>Just ain&#8217;t nothing like my river</em><br />\n<em>On such a beautiful day</em></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\"><em>Brother Jim lying right beside me</em><br />\n<em>Everything&#8217;s feeling just fine</em><br />\n<em>&#8216;Cause we&#8217;re as free as the river</em><br />\n<em>Faithful by each other&#8217;s side</em></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\"><em>The sun feels mighty good this morning</em><br />\n<em>Gonna be a good day I can see</em><br />\n<em>Its gentle rays are mighty warmin&#8217;</em><br />\n<em>Why don&#8217;t you come along with Jim and me</em></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\"><em>Plenty of fish to make good eatin&#8217;</em><br />\n<em>Lots of room upon the raft</em><br />\n<em>Now that you&#8217;re friends with the river</em><br />\n<em>Maybe you&#8217;ll never go back</em></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\"><em>Put down the load you been carrying</em><br />\n<em>Follow me and don&#8217;t look back</em><br />\n<em>Jim&#8217;s just about got supper cookin&#8217;</em><br />\n<em>Plenty of room upon the raft</em></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\"><em>Forget about time for there&#8217;s no reason</em><br />\n<em>To worry about things like that</em><br />\n<em>The days just melt into seasons</em><br />\n<em>There is no future or past</em></p>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\"><em>Summer sky is our roof top</em><br />\n<em>Travelin&#8217; on just another mile</em><br />\n<em>Don&#8217;t think I&#8217;m ever gonna stop</em><br />\n<em>Can&#8217;t do nothing now but smile and smile</em></p>\n<p>Bruce never recorded his adaptation of <em>Adventures of Huckleberry Finn</em>, but he did include some margin notes (for example, &#8220;Instead of A minor use D&#8221;) that at least tell us he envisioned &#8220;Mississippi&#8221; as a song rather than a poem.</p>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"21400\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2020/09/22/roll-of-the-dice-mississippi/mississippi_lyrics1/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics1.jpg?fit=436%2C640&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"436,640\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"mississippi_lyrics1\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics1.jpg?fit=204%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics1.jpg?fit=436%2C640&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-21400\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics1-204x300.jpg?resize=758%2C1115\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"1115\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics1.jpg?resize=204%2C300&amp;ssl=1 204w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics1.jpg?w=436&amp;ssl=1 436w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></p>\n<p><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-attachment-id=\"21401\" data-permalink=\"https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2020/09/22/roll-of-the-dice-mississippi/mississippi_lyrics2/#main\" data-orig-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics2.jpg?fit=436%2C640&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"436,640\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"mississippi_lyrics2\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics2.jpg?fit=204%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics2.jpg?fit=436%2C640&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-21401\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics2-204x300.jpg?resize=758%2C1115\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"1115\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics2.jpg?resize=204%2C300&amp;ssl=1 204w, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/mississippi_lyrics2.jpg?w=436&amp;ssl=1 436w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></p>\n<p>&#8220;Mississippi&#8221; is one of the many unrecorded, unreleased songs Bruce transcribed in his 1968 Notebook. Discover others in the series <a href=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/tag/1968-notebook/\">here</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Mississippi<br />\nNever recorded</strong><br />\n<strong>Never released</strong><br />\n<strong>Never performed</strong></p>\n<p>Looking for your favorite Bruce song? Check our full index\u00a0<a href=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/roll-of-the-dice-album-by-album/\">here</a>. New entries every week!</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Long before &#8220;The Ghost of Tom Joad,&#8221; nineteen-year-old Bruce Springsteen adapted another great work of literature into song.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 21397, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}}, "categories": [3], "tags": [1308, 340, 288], "class_